channel.description:
Hey guys, I'm gonna show you how to make NPC's say the number of players online.
(First tutorial :D)
This is really simple,
Open up NPCHandler.java look for an npc that you want to say the number of players online,
Example:
[code]                   if (npcs[i].npcType == 541) {
                        if (misc.random2(30) <= 2) {
                            npcs[i].updateRequired = true;
                            npcs[i].textUpdateRequired = true;
                            npcs[i].textUpdate = "Waffles!";[/code]
Now delete everything under
[code]if (misc.random2(30) <= 2) {[/code]
And replace it with
[code]                            npcs[i].updateRequired = true;
			    npcs[i].textUpdateRequired = true;
int players = PlayerHandler.getPlayerCount();
npcs[i].textUpdate = "Players Online: " + players;[/code]
Then save it and compile your server and you should see something like this.
[IMG]http://i996.photobucket.com/albums/af83/mowie88/Playeronline34234.jpg[/img]
